<subSubSection id="C329C4F2FFD2792012F8F91795B1F74A" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8C9779FFD2792012F8F91795B1F74A" blockId="0.[151,1436,1737,1950]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD2792012F8F917902AF6D0" bold="true" box="[151,279,1737,1764]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9474B6BFFD2792012F8F917902DF6D7" bold="true" box="[151,272,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Body form short and stout. Face slightly longer than wide, frontoclypeus expanded apically, lora small. Pronotum distinctly declivous, weakly arched, striations oblique. Forewing with 
<number id="3DFB855EFFD2792016F9F9329599F73A" box="[1174,1188,1775,1801]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number id="3DFB855EFFD2792016A4F93295E7F73A" box="[1227,1242,1775,1801]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
anteapical cells, veins spotted with white. 
<collectingCountry id="F324D7E9FFD2792013ACF8C990C3F71D" box="[451,510,1812,1838]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Hind</collectingCountry>
femoral spinulation 
<number id="3DFB855EFFD27920109FF8C9923CF71D" box="[752,769,1812,1838]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DFB855EFFD27920117CF8C99223F71D" box="[787,798,1812,1838]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
. Male pygofer elongate with tiny apical spine or acute tip or caudal margin serrate, dorsal connectives variously armed, articulating against upper margins of pygophore. Aedeagal shaft curved near apex with or without pair of slender processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
